<body>
  <div class="picker">
    <a href="../" class="back">← Back to main site</a>
    <h1>Design Versions</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">10 different takes on Piano Tuning KC. Click any to preview.</p>
    <div class="grid">
      <a href="v1-zen/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 01</div>
        <h2>Zen Minimal</h2>
        <p>Extreme whitespace, one giant CTA. Nothing between the visitor and booking. Feels calm, intentional.</p>
        <span class="tag">simplicity</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v2-letter/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 02</div>
        <h2>Warm Letter</h2>
        <p>Reads like a personal note from Jake. Handwriting-inspired fonts, warm and inviting. Like getting a letter from a friend.</p>
        <span class="tag">personal</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v3-bigbutton/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 03</div>
        <h2>Big Buttons</h2>
        <p>Maximum accessibility. Huge text, massive tap targets, high contrast. No confusion about what to do next.</p>
        <span class="tag">senior-friendly</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v4-musician/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 04</div>
        <h2>Musician Spotlight</h2>
        <p>The Voice credentials front and center. Jake-the-musician builds trust for Jake-the-tuner. Star power sells.</p>
        <span class="tag">credibility</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v5-onebook/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 05</div>
        <h2>One-Click Book</h2>
        <p>The entire page IS the booking flow. Acuity scheduler dominates. Everything else is secondary.</p>
        <span class="tag">conversion</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v6-earthy/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 06</div>
        <h2>Earthy & Warm</h2>
        <p>Rich wood tones, natural textures, warm golds. Feels like the inside of a piano — resonant and handcrafted.</p>
        <span class="tag">artisan</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v7-concert/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 07</div>
        <h2>Concert Program</h2>
        <p>Elegant like a recital program. Refined serif typography, formal but approachable. Class without pretension.</p>
        <span class="tag">elegant</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v8-neighbor/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 08</div>
        <h2>KC Neighbor</h2>
        <p>Local community pride. Jake's your neighbor who happens to tune pianos. Warm, conversational, KC-centric.</p>
        <span class="tag">community</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v9-trust/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 09</div>
        <h2>Trust Builder</h2>
        <p>Social proof heavy. Testimonial-style quotes, credentials bar, "as seen on" prominent. Let others sell for Jake.</p>
        <span class="tag">social proof</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v10-keys/" class="card">
        <div class="card-num">Version 10</div>
        <h2>Piano Keys</h2>
        <p>Playful musical motifs. Black and white key patterns, musical notation accents. Fun and artistic.</p>
        <span class="tag">artistic</span>
      </a>
      <a href="v11-instant/" class="card" style="border: 1px solid #C9A96E;">
        <div class="card-num" style="color: #C9A96E;">Version 11 — NEW</div>
        <h2>Instant Book</h2>
        <p>No calendar. No Acuity. Just type your phone number and hit Book. Jake texts you back. That's it. The simplest possible booking flow.</p>
        <span class="tag">frictionless</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
